<h1>Problem 2091 - Unknown</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>\(n > 1\) stones were placed in different cells of an infinite square grid. Each day, all stones are removed, and new stones are placed in the cells \(c\) satisfying the following condition: 
\begin{center}
``The number of stones present in either \(c\), the cell below \(c\), or the cell to the left of \(c\) on the previous day is at least 2.&#x27;&#x27;
\end{center}
Prove that after \(n\) days no stones will be left in the grid.</p>
